The paper discusses the impact of low noise amplifiers (LNAs) on the performance of massive MIMO base stations. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), systems and control (cs.SY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.MM). However, since the paper primarily focuses on the impact of LNAs on the performance of massive MIMO systems, we can reasonably assume that the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.NI, and cs.MM.
